a:43:{i:0;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"document_start";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:0;}i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"header";i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"Istovia";i:1;i:1;i:2;i:1;}i:2;i:1;}i:2;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"section_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:1;}i:2;i:1;}i:3;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1;}i:4;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"internalmedia";i:1;a:7:{i:0;s:11:"istovia.jpg";i:1;N;i:2;N;i:3;s:3:"675";i:4;N;i:5;s:5:"cache";i:6;s:7:"details";}i:2;i:23;}i:5;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:42;}i:6;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:42;}i:7;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:311:"The terrain of Istovia is cold, harsh, and rough; just like its people. The environment makes for hardy citizens, but no mortal body was built to withstand the region's bitter cold. In fact, losing entire limbs to frostbite is rather common, and has forced the people of Istovia to innovate in order to thrive. ";}i:2;i:44;}i:8;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:355;}i:9;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:355;}i:10;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:899:"Having turned their backs on the vile corruptions of magic, Istovians rely upon their god and upon their gears; and when Hroknar deems a limb unworthy of protection from the bitter cold, the people of Istovia honor him by crafting their own in its place. Intricate clockwork and gears made from the earth itself offer a fine replacement for the frail machines of the flesh that people are cursed with at birth; and once converted, how can the earth further destroy that which is of itself? Most people who have lived in Istovia for more than a handful of years have at least one mechanical limb, and some have shown such dedication to Hroknar that what remains of their original bodies is almost indistinguishable from the iron golems that are so common throughout the realm. And in return, Hroknar blesses these people with a resistance to the magical taint, whenever it should rear its ugly head. ";}i:2;i:357;}i:11;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1256;}i:12;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1256;}i:13;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:291:"The god of blood, ice, and stone is a benevolent one, and his followers in Istovia are many. The Church of Hroknar sees to it that no Child of Blood and Stone is left wanting, and acts as a guiding hand to the leaders of this great nation, as they bring Istovia's light to the world beyond. ";}i:2;i:1258;}i:14;a:3:{i:0;s:7:"p_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1549;}i:15;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"section_close";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1552;}i:16;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"header";i:1;a:3:{i:0;s:14:"Notable Places";i:1;i:3;i:2;i:1552;}i:2;i:1552;}i:17;a:3:{i:0;s:12:"section_open";i:1;a:1:{i:0;i:3;}i:2;i:1552;}i:18;a:3:{i:0;s:6:"p_open";i:1;a:0:{}i:2;i:1552;}i:19;a:3:{i:0;s:13:"internalmedia";i:1;a:7:{i:0;s:17:"brun_exterior.jpg";i:1;N;i:2;s:5:"right";i:3;s:3:"265";i:4;N;i:5;s:5:"cache";i:6;s:7:"details";}i:2;i:1578;}i:20;a:3:{i:0;s:5:"cdata";i:1;a:1:{i:0;s:1:"
